<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<?xml-stylesheet href="xsl/page.xsl" type="text/xsl" ?>

<page section="release-3.0">
  <heading>Release 3.0.1</heading>

  <content>
    <para>
      <release-info version="3.0.1" />
      The 3.0.1 release delivers <dcw /> for Mac OS X,
      minor new features, a number of bug fixes and documentation updates.
    </para>

    <table class="release-notes">
      <tr>
        <td class="head">
          <dcw /> for Mac OS X.
          <a content="download-workbench-macos" class="button download"><span>Download</span></a>
          <div class="small-links">
            <manual-link class="small" section="section.getting-started">Getting started</manual-link>
          </div>
        </td>

        <td>
          The 3.0.1 release comes with <dcw /> for Mac OS X.

          <a content="download-workbench-macos"> 
            <img class="pic rn" src="img/workbench-macos.png" alt="Carrot2 Clustering Workbench for Mac OS" /></a>
        </td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td class="head">
          Advanced options in <c2 /> <wa />
          <carrot2-webapp-link class="button view"><span>View online</span></carrot2-webapp-link>
          <div class="small-links">
            <a content="download-webapp" class="small"><span>Download WAR</span></a>
          </div>
        </td>

        <td>
          <c2 /> <wa /> exposes some more advanced search options for each document source.

          <carrot2-webapp-link>
            <img class="pic rn" src="img/webapp-advanced-options.png" alt="Carrot2 Web Application, advanced search options" /></carrot2-webapp-link>
        </td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td class="head">
          Bug fixes and performance improvmenets
        </td>

        <td>
          For a complete list, please see a <a
          href="http://issues.carrot2.org/browse/CARROT/fixforversion/10130">list
          of fixed JIRA issues</a>.
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <hr />

    <p>
      For more new features, please see <a content="release-3.0-notes">release 3.0 notes</a>.
    </p>
  </content>
</page>
